 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3327/resize-floating-windows-on-start/?answer=3328#post-id-3328</link><description>The key is to make a matcher that works. Have a look in the userguide at the [for_window command](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_arbitrary_commands_for_specific_windows_for_window). 

Here is a nice [solution for a drop down terminal](https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2420/dropdown-terminal-in-i3/?answer=2626#post-id-2626). 
</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Jan 2014 06:21:36 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3327/resize-floating-windows-on-start/?answer=3328#post-id-3328</guid></item><item><title>Answer by jared for &lt;p&gt;I want to turn URxvt into a drop down terminal, something similar to guake.  but I want it to be a certain size. I set floating&lt;em&gt;maximum and floating&lt;/em&gt;minimum_size to the size I wanted, (1366x350) but obviously that turned even the popup dialogs into that size. Is there anyway to resize URxvt automatically without resizing all floating windows?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3327/resize-floating-windows-on-start/?answer=3333#post-id-3333</link><description>I was not aware you could use the resize options under the for_window command I thought they were only for keybindings. That solved my problem.</description><pubDate>Fri, 31 Jan 2014 15:51:49 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3327/resize-floating-windows-on-start/?answer=3333#post-id-3333</guid></item><item><title>Answer by jared for &lt;p&gt;I want to turn URxvt into a drop down terminal, something similar to guake.  but I want it to be a certain size. I set floating&lt;em&gt;maximum and floating&lt;/em&gt;minimum_size to the size I wanted, (1366x350) but obviously that turned even the popup dialogs into that size. Is there anyway to resize URxvt automatically without resizing all floating windows?&lt;/p&gt;
